      "name": "from_the_venue",
      "title": null
    },
    {
      "attribution": null,
      "body": "The reopening is finally here! Maison Pickle will be open for reservations and walk ins beginning at 4pm on Wednesday 3/11.\n\nWHAT TO KNOW BEFORE DINING\n❖  In order to allow as many guests to enjoy dining with us, we ask that you limit your dining time to an hour and fifteen for Brunch and an hour and a half for Dinner.\n❖  We will seat you as close to your reservation time as possible.\n❖  We ask that you arrive complete with your party to avoid crowding and allow for safe dining space.\n❖  We ask that you arrive on time as we will only hold reservations for up to 15 minutes.  After 15 minutes, your reservation will be placed on the waitlist for the next available table. \n\nRESERVATION GUIDELINES\n❖  We accept reservations for up to 11 guests.  Please contact our events team for parties of 12 and more by emailing info@maisonpickle.com\n",
      "display": {
        "type": "text"
      },
      "icon": {
        "url": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/resy.com/images/icons/info.svg"
      },
      "locale": {
        "language": "en-us"
      },
      "name": "need_to_know",
      "title": "Need to Know"
    },
    {
      "attribution": null,
      "body": "Maison Pickle is centered around a classic American staple: The French Dip sandwich. Part-cheap eat, part-culinary-innovation, The French Dip is a backbone of the urban dining scene since its early days in 1910s Los Angeles at the Cole’s Pacific Electric Buffet, or Phillipe’s (depending on who you’re talking to). Comfortable, inventive and inviting — the pleasures of American restauranting — are reimagined for a contemporary urban experience in Manhattan’s West 80s.",
      "display": {
        "type": "text"
      },
